(Adapted from Douban Read's work
"Smile Code" by Zu Yue)

24
00:01:41,160 --> 00:01:44,930
=Episode 33=

25
00:01:55,190 --> 00:01:56,160
You're just in time.

26
00:01:56,750 --> 00:01:57,390
Job's done.

27
00:01:58,230 --> 00:01:59,190
Here's your work badge back.

28
00:01:59,800 --> 00:02:01,090
Send me the remaining payment soon.

29
00:02:01,240 --> 00:02:02,400
Don't worry, you'll get every cent.

30
00:02:02,400 --> 00:02:04,210
We're having a wrap party
for the love reality show tonight.

31
00:02:04,230 --> 00:02:04,760
You should come.

32
00:02:04,790 --> 00:02:05,710
The boss wants to meet you.

33
00:02:07,150 --> 00:02:08,550
Tell your boss

34
00:02:08,910 --> 00:02:09,750
that I'm done

35
00:02:09,950 --> 00:02:10,790
taking

36
00:02:10,950 --> 00:02:11,590
rough-cut jobs.

37
00:02:11,790 --> 00:02:12,350
From now on,

38
00:02:12,400 --> 00:02:13,330
I'll be picking my projects.

39
00:02:14,190 --> 00:02:16,070
Who was it that said,

40
00:02:16,190 --> 00:02:17,510
"Rough cuts are still editing"?

41
00:02:17,870 --> 00:02:19,750
Now that the job's done,
you're nitpicking?

42
00:02:19,750 --> 00:02:20,600
That's not what I mean.

43
00:02:20,630 --> 00:02:21,830
I appreciate the opportunity,

44
00:02:21,910 --> 00:02:22,930
but I've been working nonstop

45
00:02:22,960 --> 00:02:24,230
for three and a half months.

46
00:02:24,430 --> 00:02:25,750
I need a break.

47
00:02:26,270 --> 00:02:26,830
Plus,

48
00:02:26,830 --> 00:02:28,390
I've got my bar to manage.

49
00:02:29,590 --> 00:02:29,990
Fine.

50
00:02:30,680 --> 00:02:31,270
All right, then.

51
00:02:33,790 --> 00:02:34,390
But seriously,

52
00:02:35,120 --> 00:02:36,230
hurry up with that final payment.

53
00:02:38,150 --> 00:02:39,270
I'm strapped for cash.

54
00:02:47,470 --> 00:02:48,790
Sorry, sorry.

55
00:02:49,190 --> 00:02:50,150
Did you wait long?

56
00:02:50,470 --> 00:02:51,790
I was in a meeting the whole time.

57
00:02:53,510 --> 00:02:54,070
It's no big deal.

58
00:02:54,430 --> 00:02:55,950
I got you a sandwich to hold you over.

59
00:02:56,350 --> 00:02:57,670
Save some room for cake tonight.

60
00:02:59,190 --> 00:03:00,230
Before we pick up the cake,

61
00:03:00,310 --> 00:03:02,110
can you take me to buy a gift first?

62
00:03:03,750 --> 00:03:05,750
Didn't you organize
Yu Dule's birthday party?

63
00:03:06,350 --> 00:03:07,750
How do you not have a gift yet?

64
00:03:09,720 --> 00:03:10,440
I didn't buy one yet.

65
00:03:10,590 --> 00:03:11,190
Did you?

66
00:03:13,550 --> 00:03:14,030
A hard drive.

67
00:03:14,630 --> 00:03:15,670
He edits videos, doesn't he?

68
00:03:15,700 --> 00:03:16,870
It'll probably come in handy.

69
00:03:17,470 --> 00:03:19,350
You didn't need to get him two presents.

70
00:03:19,710 --> 00:03:21,270
Now I seem thoughtless.

71
00:03:21,480 --> 00:03:22,640
Give me one to pass off as mine.

72
00:03:23,470 --> 00:03:25,870
The graphics card is from Lu Ming.

73
00:03:26,110 --> 00:03:26,990
He couldn't make it

74
00:03:27,430 --> 00:03:29,470
and asked us to give Yu Dule
his regards on his behalf.

75
00:03:30,110 --> 00:03:31,550
You even contacted Mr. Lu?

76
00:03:31,990 --> 00:03:33,150
How's he doing?

77
00:03:34,670 --> 00:03:35,390
He's doing well.

78
00:03:36,030 --> 00:03:37,710
He's focused on fulfilling orders
at the factory.

79
00:03:38,590 --> 00:03:39,870
I heard he's so busy

80
00:03:40,070 --> 00:03:41,360
that he barely has time to sleep.

81
00:03:42,350 --> 00:03:44,270
He was happy
about Ounce's grand opening.

82
00:03:44,630 --> 00:03:45,670
He joked that Fuzzy has no luck

83
00:03:46,190 --> 00:03:47,790
with comedy shows

84
00:03:47,880 --> 00:03:49,810
and said he'll turn the place
into a script game venue

85
00:03:49,990 --> 00:03:51,110
once the lease ends.

86
00:03:53,750 --> 00:03:54,430
Liang Daiwen,

87
00:03:55,590 --> 00:03:56,430
have you noticed

88
00:03:57,390 --> 00:03:59,470
that all my friends
have become your friends?

89
00:04:02,390 --> 00:04:03,790
Well, my dad always asks about you first

90
00:04:03,910 --> 00:04:05,190
when he calls me now.

91
00:04:14,630 --> 00:04:15,150
That reminds me.

92
00:04:15,630 --> 00:04:16,710
Should we invite

93
00:04:17,590 --> 00:04:19,190
Guan Xingxin too?

94
00:04:20,990 --> 00:04:21,750
What do you think?

95
00:04:24,790 --> 00:04:25,830
I think

96
00:04:26,510 --> 00:04:27,110
we should.

97
00:04:28,190 --> 00:04:29,190
That's right.

98
00:04:29,590 --> 00:04:31,110
You're learning, robot.

99
00:04:31,150 --> 00:04:32,260
You'll be a pro in no time.

100
00:04:34,320 --> 00:04:39,390
(Guan Xingxin)

101
00:04:40,950 --> 00:04:42,030
Do you have plans

102
00:04:42,150 --> 00:04:42,910
tonight?

103
00:04:43,350 --> 00:04:44,510
Still on set.

104
00:04:44,770 --> 00:04:46,110
The last two episodes got moved up,

105
00:04:46,150 --> 00:04:47,790
so we're filming them today.

106
00:04:48,390 --> 00:04:49,750
There's a wrap party later.

107
00:04:51,950 --> 00:04:53,670
It's Yu Dule's birthday today.

108
00:04:54,270 --> 00:04:55,230
If you're free,

109
00:04:56,070 --> 00:04:56,710
you should drop by.

110
00:04:59,030 --> 00:05:01,270
Did he ask you to invite me?

111
00:05:06,230 --> 00:05:07,390
He doesn't know,

112
00:05:08,150 --> 00:05:09,510
but he'd definitely want you there.

113
00:05:14,070 --> 00:05:15,090
(Crazy for you,
crashing into walls for you!)

114
00:05:15,090 --> 00:05:15,850
(Happy birthday!)

115
00:05:15,850 --> 00:05:16,660
(Congratulations
to the young master of Ounce!)

116
00:05:16,660 --> 00:05:17,530
(Best wishes
Forever young)

117
00:05:17,530 --> 00:05:20,560
(Happy birthday, Good Luck)

118
00:05:25,830 --> 00:05:26,990
Should we call him to ask

119
00:05:27,230 --> 00:05:28,190
where he is?

120
00:05:28,660 --> 00:05:30,320
If we wait any longer,
you'll finish all of them.

121
00:05:31,350 --> 00:05:31,910
No way.

122
00:05:32,590 --> 00:05:33,990
That would ruin the surprise.

123
00:05:36,030 --> 00:05:37,550
Why does this feel like
we're planning a heist

124
00:05:38,670 --> 00:05:40,150
instead of a party?

125
00:05:40,950 --> 00:05:41,630
You don't understand.

126
00:05:42,070 --> 00:05:44,310
Mr. Yu's parents were always busy

127
00:05:44,470 --> 00:05:45,270
when he was a kid,

128
00:05:45,710 --> 00:05:46,390
so

129
00:05:46,560 --> 00:05:48,200
he's never really
celebrated his birthday.

130
00:05:48,590 --> 00:05:50,470
Every time we suggested it,

131
00:05:50,830 --> 00:05:51,510
he turned us down,

132
00:05:51,830 --> 00:05:53,160
saying it was too sentimental.

133
00:05:53,350 --> 00:05:53,870
So, this time,

134
00:05:53,990 --> 00:05:54,990
we're throwing him a big one.

135
00:05:57,510 --> 00:05:59,110
You invited him out on his birthday.

136
00:06:00,270 --> 00:06:01,710
Surely he'll know something's up.

137
00:06:02,830 --> 00:06:04,190
That's where you're wrong.

138
00:06:04,750 --> 00:06:05,750
Humans do silly things

139
00:06:05,750 --> 00:06:07,550
to create happiness

140
00:06:07,550 --> 00:06:08,790
for each other.

141
00:06:09,430 --> 00:06:10,470
Learn from this, robot.

142
00:06:15,110 --> 00:06:15,710
He's here.

143
00:06:33,790 --> 00:06:35,190
Happy birthday!

144
00:06:36,630 --> 00:06:37,870
Why is it you?

145
00:06:39,860 --> 00:06:40,790
I've foiled your plan,

146
00:06:41,310 --> 00:06:42,310
Ms. Gu.

147
00:06:44,630 --> 00:06:45,070
Well…

148
00:06:46,710 --> 00:06:47,190
Should we

149
00:06:47,710 --> 00:06:48,390
try again?

150
00:06:49,350 --> 00:06:50,110
Forget it.

151
00:06:50,470 --> 00:06:51,510
It's a waste of my emotions.

152
00:06:52,070 --> 00:06:52,510
Come on.

153
00:06:52,590 --> 00:06:53,270
Let's cut the cake.

154
00:07:00,990 --> 00:07:01,750
Cut it properly.

155
00:07:02,270 --> 00:07:03,430
If you mess up,

156
00:07:03,830 --> 00:07:05,390
no daughters for you.

157
00:07:06,590 --> 00:07:07,190
Gu Yi,

158
00:07:07,310 --> 00:07:08,430
how can you

159
00:07:08,430 --> 00:07:09,550
curse me so?

160
00:07:10,710 --> 00:07:11,750
Why is that a curse?

161
00:07:12,270 --> 00:07:14,470
He's secretly a total "girl dad".

162
00:07:14,950 --> 00:07:16,190
It worked wonders

163
00:07:16,190 --> 00:07:16,830
on Mr. Lu

164
00:07:16,850 --> 00:07:17,670
during his birthday.

165
00:07:17,670 --> 00:07:18,550
That's different.

166
00:07:19,030 --> 00:07:20,430
He already has

167
00:07:20,430 --> 00:07:21,430
an adorable daughter.

168
00:07:21,970 --> 00:07:22,370
Shut up.

169
00:07:24,870 --> 00:07:26,110
Cut it nicely.

170
00:07:43,110 --> 00:07:44,190
Not bad.

171
00:07:44,350 --> 00:07:44,830
Right?

172
00:07:47,510 --> 00:07:48,030
And my presents?

173
00:07:54,550 --> 00:07:55,750
Gee, thanks, Gu Yi.

174
00:07:56,950 --> 00:07:58,910
I can immediately tell
it's a last-minute from a mall.

175
00:07:58,910 --> 00:07:59,990
See? Am I right?

176
00:08:00,270 --> 00:08:01,150
How'd you know?

177
00:08:02,190 --> 00:08:04,310
Last year, I gave you a microphone.

178
00:08:04,420 --> 00:08:05,790
It was a last-minute from the mall too.

179
00:08:06,750 --> 00:08:08,270
Guess our minds think alike.

180
00:08:09,870 --> 00:08:10,990
The graphics card is from Mr. Lu.

181
00:08:11,200 --> 00:08:12,030
And this is from me.

182
00:08:13,510 --> 00:08:15,030
How unoriginal.

183
00:08:15,590 --> 00:08:16,950
Straight into the editing room

184
00:08:16,950 --> 00:08:18,190
for me, huh?

185
00:08:19,230 --> 00:08:19,670
Thanks.

186
00:08:23,830 --> 00:08:24,350
It's okay.

187
00:08:24,470 --> 00:08:24,910
Um…

188
00:08:25,030 --> 00:08:25,870
Let's serve the cake.

189
00:08:27,150 --> 00:08:27,790
Wait.

190
00:08:28,310 --> 00:08:30,110
What about
those fortune cookies we bought?

191
00:08:30,750 --> 00:08:32,190
Let's write down our wishes.

192
00:08:32,430 --> 00:08:33,950
No cookies left.

193
00:08:34,510 --> 00:08:35,350
You ate them all.

194
00:08:35,460 --> 00:08:36,670
Perfect. No need to write anything.

195
00:08:36,670 --> 00:08:37,440
It's childish anyway…

196
00:08:37,440 --> 00:08:37,950
Write.

197
00:08:38,910 --> 00:08:41,190
Make up for your poor
childhood memories.

198
00:08:41,710 --> 00:08:42,590
Let's write them.

199
00:08:42,590 --> 00:08:43,410
I'll go get the paper.

200
00:08:49,920 --> 00:08:50,980
Why not prepare beforehand?

201
00:08:50,990 --> 00:08:52,200
Now you have to run backstage.

202
00:08:52,310 --> 00:08:53,070
Wasting my time.

203
00:09:13,470 --> 00:09:14,590
Are you writing an essay?

204
00:09:15,910 --> 00:09:16,870
What did you write? Show me.

205
00:09:17,150 --> 00:09:17,790
Show you what?

206
00:09:17,950 --> 00:09:19,350
It won't come true if I let you see it.

207
00:09:19,470 --> 00:09:20,630
And you said this was childish.

208
00:09:20,870 --> 00:09:22,230
You're taking it awfully seriously now.

209
00:09:23,830 --> 00:09:24,990
I… I'll go grab a case of beer.

210
00:09:38,630 --> 00:09:39,230
Ms. Gu,

211
00:09:39,870 --> 00:09:41,230
care to exchange wishes?

212
00:09:41,950 --> 00:09:43,710
Why bother? The birthday boy's gone.

213
00:09:43,710 --> 00:09:44,390
Here, just read it.

214
00:09:47,950 --> 00:09:51,110
"I hope Mr. Yu becomes
the world's number one editor…"

215
00:09:51,710 --> 00:09:52,750
Video editor.

216
00:09:54,110 --> 00:09:54,550
That's it?

217
00:09:55,390 --> 00:09:56,110
That's it.

218
00:09:56,240 --> 00:09:57,300
What else would I write?

219
00:09:57,360 --> 00:09:58,400
What did you write?

220
00:10:01,910 --> 00:10:03,070
My cosmic order.

221
00:10:04,870 --> 00:10:06,070
I hope next time

222
00:10:06,070 --> 00:10:07,250
(Cosmic Order, Liang X Gu)

223
00:10:07,470 --> 00:10:08,550
you won't reject my proposal.

224
00:10:46,020 --> 00:10:47,600
I finished filming
the love reality show.

225
00:10:52,070 --> 00:10:52,550
I know.

226
00:10:55,350 --> 00:10:56,270
Let's head back.

227
00:10:56,820 --> 00:10:58,120
Let's not talk about that.

228
00:11:01,990 --> 00:11:02,990
In your heart,

229
00:11:03,670 --> 00:11:05,110
I've always been
on the rocks, haven't I?

230
00:11:10,790 --> 00:11:11,870
When we broke up,

231
00:11:13,670 --> 00:11:14,790
you said I didn't love anyone.

232
00:11:16,910 --> 00:11:18,390
You've long thought I was selfish

233
00:11:19,390 --> 00:11:20,550
and knew this would be

234
00:11:20,950 --> 00:11:22,470
our outcome,

235
00:11:23,030 --> 00:11:23,630
didn't you?

236
00:11:30,390 --> 00:11:31,190
It's all in the past.

237
00:11:32,290 --> 00:11:33,150
Let's not dwell on it.

238
00:11:38,350 --> 00:11:39,270
I know

239
00:11:39,670 --> 00:11:40,630
you're disappointed in me.

240
00:11:42,630 --> 00:11:44,110
I'm disappointed in myself, too.

241
00:11:47,630 --> 00:11:49,670
It's my fault
our relationship fell apart.

242
00:11:50,870 --> 00:11:52,190
There's no point

243
00:11:52,552 --> 00:11:53,830
in forcing a reconciliation.

244
00:11:56,790 --> 00:11:57,830
My parents and I

245
00:11:58,470 --> 00:11:59,630
won't hurt you anymore.

246
00:12:02,670 --> 00:12:03,270
So,

247
00:12:06,190 --> 00:12:07,990
let's end things here.

248
00:12:10,430 --> 00:12:11,670
I respect your decision.

249
00:12:23,630 --> 00:12:25,910
No one had ever
given me cornflowers before.

250
00:12:27,390 --> 00:12:28,510
I'll always remember

251
00:12:28,710 --> 00:12:30,070
the days we spent together.

252
00:12:31,310 --> 00:12:31,950
Yu Dule,

253
00:12:33,270 --> 00:12:35,230
thank you for being by my side
for so long.

254
00:12:41,390 --> 00:12:42,230
Happy birthday.

255
00:12:54,630 --> 00:12:55,310
Actually,

256
00:12:58,430 --> 00:13:00,390
I've never blamed you or your parents,

257
00:13:02,390 --> 00:13:03,070
so

258
00:13:07,030 --> 00:13:08,030
don't blame yourself either.

259
00:14:18,470 --> 00:14:19,070
Mr. Yu,

260
00:14:19,630 --> 00:14:20,390
where do you live?

261
00:14:20,680 --> 00:14:21,700
I don't have an address.

262
00:14:24,630 --> 00:14:25,190
Mr. Yu?

263
00:14:27,310 --> 00:14:27,790
Let me do it.

264
00:14:27,920 --> 00:14:28,920
I'll put in the address.

265
00:14:36,350 --> 00:14:37,310
Now that the show is over,

266
00:14:38,030 --> 00:14:38,830
what's next for you?

267
00:14:42,270 --> 00:14:43,790
There are plenty
of entertainment companies

268
00:14:44,030 --> 00:14:46,030
and MCNs that want to sign me,

269
00:14:47,150 --> 00:14:48,070
but I turned them all down.

270
00:14:50,070 --> 00:14:51,510
After these past months,

271
00:14:52,750 --> 00:14:55,110
I finally understand what Shen meant

272
00:14:55,990 --> 00:14:57,590
by accepting oneself.

273
00:15:01,230 --> 00:15:02,470
I want to live my own life,

274
00:15:02,950 --> 00:15:03,710
for myself.

275
00:15:06,150 --> 00:15:07,750
Don't worry. I'll be fine.

276
00:15:11,950 --> 00:15:13,470
We'll all get better from here on out.

277
00:15:15,790 --> 00:15:17,550
By the way, I saw what Yu Dule

278
00:15:18,750 --> 00:15:19,950
wrote on the fortune paper he hid.

279
00:15:20,910 --> 00:15:22,030
He wrote your name.

280
00:15:24,830 --> 00:15:25,790
He hopes

281
00:15:28,350 --> 00:15:29,910
you'll always live in the light.

282
00:15:48,910 --> 00:15:49,590
What are you doing?

283
00:15:51,990 --> 00:15:53,110
Are you taking advantage of me?

284
00:15:54,470 --> 00:15:55,550
Take off your shoes.

285
00:15:55,760 --> 00:15:57,150
Are you going to sleep with them on?

286
00:15:59,590 --> 00:16:00,190
Go.

287
00:16:01,350 --> 00:16:04,190
Grab my pajamas for me.

288
00:16:14,190 --> 00:16:14,830
Gu Yi,

289
00:16:15,710 --> 00:16:16,750
are you a gecko?

290
00:16:18,030 --> 00:16:18,630
Don't move.

291
00:16:19,870 --> 00:16:20,430
This is…

292
00:16:21,790 --> 00:16:22,630
a robbery.

293
00:16:24,150 --> 00:16:25,060
What are you robbing?

294
00:16:31,030 --> 00:16:31,950
Your virtue.

295
00:16:58,120 --> 00:17:00,100
